  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Senior army officer involved in Yakgahapitiya incident relieved of duties",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Vikum Liyanage has relieved the officer involved in the incident at Yakgahapitiya Petrol Station of all his duties with immediate effect until the 5-member Court of Inquiry\u2019s recommendations are received.",
        "A parallel military investigation of the Sri Lanka Army Corps of Military Police (SLACMP) with regard to the incident is also underway recording statements, the Sri Lanka Army said today.",
        "The Security Force Headquarters - West on Monday (4) appointed a five-member Court of Inquiry, headed by a Brigade Commander to investigate into the issue, related to the Senior Officer\u2019s conduct and to make its recommendations.",
        "A video recorded using a mobile phone, showing an army officer kicking a person on the chest at a fuel station, had been widely circulated on social media recently prompting the internal investigation."
      ],
